    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Metal racks, usually comprising a round metal band supporting multiple hooks, that were hung from the ceiling or another support and used to hang meat. The racks are usually historical. Antique crown meat racks are sometimes used in modern kitchens as pot racks</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
